==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exuviæ
<hw>Ex*u"vi*⟦ae⟧</hw>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L., fr.
<ets>exuere</ets> to draw out or off, to pull off.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>Cast skins, shells, or coverings of animals;
any parts of animals which are shed or cast off, as the skins of snakes,
the shells of lobsters, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>The fossil shells and other
remains which animals have left in the strata of the earth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exuvial</ent>⟦br⟧
